	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />-choose an initial direction for the ball away from the player
<br />-increment/decrement the ball in X/Y directions (Y direction depending on player side), until it comes into contact with the ceiling, floor, opponent's paddle or goal
<br />-if the ball comes into contact with the ceiling or floor, invert the Y direction
<br />-if the ball comes into contact with the opponent's paddle, invert the X direction
<br />
<br />Some games appear to deflect the ball at an angle based on where the ball hits the paddle, I guess since the paddle can't be tilted, but this doesn't make sense in real life (not that the rest does).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


