	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The deflection angle sometimes approaches 180 degrees at the closest paddle edge to the ball, 90 at the middle, 0 at the furthest edge, it really depends on the implementation. And it does appear that really old games have fixed angles.
<br />
<br />Here's the actual implementation:
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.cityofberwyn.com/schematics/PDF/PONGSchem.pdf">http://www.cityofberwyn.com/schematics/ ... GSchem.pdf</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />And an analog pong-like: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.pong-story.com/eaus0576.htm">http://www.pong-story.com/eaus0576.htm</a><!-- m -->

		

		</td>
	</tr>
